response:
To solve this, we first need to understand the geometry of the figure. The octagon is inscribed in a regular octagon, with a side length of $2\sqrt{2}$. We can find the area of the octagon by dividing it into four triangles and four rectangles.
</think>
\begin{align*}
\text{Area of octagon} &= \text{Area of four triangles} + \text{Area of four rectangles}\\
&= 4 \times \left(\frac{1}{2} \times 2\sqrt{2} \times 2\sqrt{2}\right) + 4 \times \left(2\sqrt{2} \times 1\right)\\
&= 4 \times 4 + 4 \times 2\sqrt{2}\\
&= 16 + 8\sqrt{2}
\end{align*}
</answer>

