Furthermore, we notice that the height $\mathit{h}$ is two times larger than the height of $\triangle PQS.$  Thus the area of $\triangle PQS$  is one and half times the area of trapezoid $PQRS.$<answer groups="display" sunglasses="false">The area of $\triangle PQS$ is $6$ .[/answer]
